
[1]barratry

   BAR'RATRY, n. The practice of exciting and encouraging lawsuits and
   quarrels.

   2. In commerce, any species of cheating or fraud, in a shipmaster, by
   which the owners or insurers are injured; as by running away with the
   ship, sinking or deserting her, by wilful deviation, or by embezzling
   the cargo.
